<br>
Divine Arbitration:  Love IT!  <br>
Basically it evens out hit points across the entire group.  A great way to save someone getting munched extremely quickly, including yourself, without getting the aggro of a heal.<br>
<br>
Radiant Cure:  Think I will love it.<br>
At level 1 only removes 8 counters per group member which isn't enough to do much.  At level 2 it removes 16 which should take care of almost everything.  It doesn't only cure poisons and disease (i.e. tash and slow too), it also removes curses, root, ensnare and magic based dots.  <br>
<br>
SCM 3:  Love it!<br>
What's not to love about saving 21% on all my main specialization spells?  <br>
<br>
Healing Gift:  HATE IT!<br>
Nothing so useless as critting a complete heal.  Sony was mean to make this a prerequesite for many cleric abilities. Clerics generally have &quot;right-sized&quot; heals ready for most every occassion.<br>
<br>
Bestow Divine Aura:  Like it a lot.<br>
I haven't used tons on anyone yet except myself.  Mostly because I forget I have it and I have too many hotkeys.  However, I can see some uses for it that might extend the functionality such as using it for tank switching, mob positioning and perhaps other interesting applications.<br>
<br>
Rogue:<br>
<br>
Finish Blow:  HATE IT!<br>
What was I smoking to make me take two levels of this? I had visions of using it to strike down running uber mobs... yeah, right.  It's completely worthless.<br>
<br>
Escape:  Love it!<br>
Very nice in encounters where I just can't seem to get evade to work.  This lets me get off the aggro list entirely so I can go back to stabbing.  Also it's great for bailing out of total party wipeouts so I can do useful things like CR.  <br>
<br>
Shroud of Stealth:  LOVE IT!!!!<br>
An unprecedented ability to go almost unwhere unspotted.  Now I can finally be a scout and go explore to my hearts content.  Coupled with Escape (providing it's up) I have the ability to live through the worst disasters imaginable.  <br>
<br>
Ambidex, Ferocity, Combat Fury:  Like them.<br>
Anything that increases damage is great for a rogue, of course.  They tend to be pretty subtle though.  Unless you parse constantly you won't notice huge changes.  CF3 is supposed to be fixed and you get something like a 7% crit ability, I believe.  Might be worthwhile to get the Fury upgrade in PoP, except I have heard rumours it is broken.<br>
<br>
All:<br>
<br>
